SIMPLE: spiny
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spiny
<hw>Spin"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Spine</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of spines; thorny; <as>as,
a <ex>spiny</ex> tree</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Like a spine in shape; slender.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Spiny</xex> grasshoppers sit chirping.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Fig.: Abounding with difficulties or
annoyances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>spiny</qex> deserts of scholastic philosophy.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Warburton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spiny lobster</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>Same as
<cref>Rock lobster</cref>, under <er>Rock</er>. See also
<er>Lobster</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spiny</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spiny
<hw>Spin"y</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>See <er>Spinny</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
